<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881013-0124 </DOCNO><HL> Manville's Mill Expansion Plan </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MAN MVL </CO><IN> BCY </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Manville Corp. said it plans to spend $22 million to expand its paper and pulp mill in Igaras, Brazil.    The company said the plan has been approved by its board and a federal bankruptcy court. Manville has been operating under protection from creditors under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code while it tries to work out a plan to compensate victims of asbestos-related diseases. </TEXT></DOC>